@{b}Usage@{ub}
***************

There are 2 ways to use Mnemosyne:

  Using the CLI (Command Line Interface)
  --------------------------------------

   To use Mnemosyne from the CLI, just type on your shell:

     @{b}Mnemosyne <path>@{ub}

   Where <path> is the path to the directory you want to scan.



  Using the GUI (Graphical User Interface)
  -----------------------------------------

  To use Mnemosyne from the GUI, just double click on the Mnemosyne icon
  and using the GUI, click on the button to select the directory you want
  after that click on the "Scan" button to start scanning the directory.

  When the scanning is finished, it will show you the results.

  @{b}For more information about the GUI, 
  please check the Github Wiki page where it will 
  include images and more information about the GUI. @{ub}




